---
import { Link } from "@avaya/neo-react";
import { Description, PageTitle, PageleteSection } from "components/astro";
---

<PageleteSection>
  <PageTitle>FAQs</PageTitle>
  <Description>
    Get immediate answers to your questions. You can also visit
    <Link
      inline
      href="https://spaces.avayacloud.com/spaces/5fdab55a49115337dfabe103"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      Spaces for Neo Community
    </Link>
     for additional answers.
  </Description>
</PageleteSection>

<section>
  <div>
    <h3>What is Neo?</h3>
    <p>
      Neo is Avayaâ€™s Design System. It is an open-source design system for all
      Avaya products. It provides a consistent look across all digital forms.
      Neo components include accessibility to help our products reach the
      widest audience, and to satisfy international regulations.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>Why should my application use Neo?</h3>
    <p>
      Neo uses a set of standardized components and UX best practices to ensure
      a consistent and easy to use experience across our product ecosystem.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>What are guidelines?</h3>
    <p>
      Guidelines provide an overview of different key topics related to our
      design system, as well as best practices. Visit the <Link
        inline
        href="/guidelines/overview"
      >
        Guidelines page
      </Link>
       to get the whole picture.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>What are components and how do I use them?</h3>
    <p>
      Components represent commonly used UI elements and are the building blocks
      for application design. A block of code that defines a UI feature or
      element that can be reused. Each component has a detailed explanation of
      how to use the component. View the
      <Link inline href="/guidelines/overview">Components section</Link>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>How do I install Neo?</h3>
    <p>
      Neo components for different platforms can be downloaded from
      <Link inline href="/docs/setup">Setup Neo</Link>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>Which browsers does Neo support?</h3>
    <p>Neo is set to support the latest 2 versions of modern browsers.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>Where can I download the icons?</h3>
    <p>
      Neo Icons are available in SVG and PNG formats from the
      <Link inline href="/icons">Icons page</Link>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>How can I download the Noto Sans typeface?</h3>
    <p>
      Noto Sans is pre-installed in the web versions of Neo. For other
      platforms, it can be downloaded at
      <Link
        inline
        href="https://fonts.google.com/noto"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Google Noto Fonts
      </Link>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>What development languages are supported?</h3>
    <p>
      Neo has CSS and React support today, with Angular and Vue versions coming
      soon.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Can multiple versions of Neo be used within the same project?</h3>
    <p>Always use the latest version to avoid potential conflicts.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>How should the keyboard interaction work for each component?</h3>
    <p>
      Refer to the keyboard interactions page, or the specific component page
      for a list of standard keyboard interactions.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>Where do I start to make my application accessible?</h3>
    <p>
      Read through the <Link inline href="/accessibility/principles">
        Accessibility
      </Link> guidelines for an introduction and some hot tips. The <Link
        inline
        href="/guidelines/overview"
      >
        Guidelines page
      </Link>
       is also a great place to look for ideas.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>How do I make my white labelled product adopt Neo?</h3>
    <p>
      Depending on the flexibility of the product, use our font (Noto Sans), as
      well as our color system and icons where possible.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>Where do I report an issue with Neo?</h3>
    <p>
      All bugs should be reported in the Avaya Space
      <Link
        inline
        href="https://spaces.avayacloud.com/spaces/63d91605385d4693560107ca"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Neo Design System Feedback
      </Link>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>When can I expect a response after a bug is reported?</h3>
    <p>You should receive a response within one business day.</p>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>How do I receive feature and bug updates?</h3>
    <p>
      You can join the Avaya Space
      <Link
        inline
        href="https://spaces.avayacloud.com/spaces/63d91605385d4693560107ca"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        Neo Design System Feedback
      </Link>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    row-gap: 4rem;
    margin-bottom: 6rem;
  }
  section div {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    row-gap: 0.75rem;
  }
  section div h3 {
    font-family: noto-sans;
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 40px;
    letter-spacing: 0em;
    text-align: left;
  }

  section div p {
    font-family: noto-sans;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 24px;
    letter-spacing: 0em;
    text-align: left;
  }

  p a.neo-link.neo-link__inline {
    padding: 0;
    display: inline-block;
  }
</style>
